cryptexctl-path(1)           General Commands Manual          cryptexctl-path(1)

NAME
     cryptexctl path â€“ return search paths for a session

SYNOPSIS
     cryptexctl path [--cryptex BUNDLE_ID] --path
     cryptexctl path [--cryptex BUNDLE_ID] --search-path SEARCH_PATH

DESCRIPTION
     cryptexctl path is used to generate search paths for content from cryptexes
     for the user calling it.

OPTIONS
     A list of options with their descriptions.


     -c | --cryptex BUNDLE_ID
             Limits results to the cryptex with the specified Bundle ID.

     -s | --session
             Specifies the UUID of the session you want to search instead of the
             current user.

     -S | --search-path SEARCH_PATH
             Provided a colon delimited list of paths, returns all instances of
             those subpaths within applicable cryptexes.  -S
             /usr:/Library:/invalid

     -p | --path
             Use a default SEARCH_PATH appropriate for inserting into the PATH
             environment variable.

SEE ALSO
     cryptexctl(1), cryptexctl-session(1), cryptex(5),

HISTORY
     Introduced in macOS 13.5

